### ⏳ TASK 3 — Create Repository Layer (PENDING)
Create lib/repositories/ with these files and methods:

user_repository.dart
  getUser(String userId) → Future<UserModel>
  updateUser(UserModel user) → Future<void>
  watchUser(String userId) → Stream<UserModel>

product_repository.dart
  getProducts() → Future<List<ProductModel>>
  getProductById(String id) → Future<ProductModel>
  getProductsByCategory(String categoryId) → Future<List<ProductModel>>
  addProduct(ProductModel p) → Future<void>
  updateProduct(ProductModel p) → Future<void>
  deleteProduct(String id) → Future<void>
  searchProducts(String query) → Future<List<ProductModel>>
  getCachedProducts() → Future<List<ProductModel>>     ← from SQLite
  cacheProducts(List<ProductModel> p) → Future<void>   ← to SQLite

order_repository.dart
  createOrder(OrderModel o) → Future<String>
  getOrdersByUser(String userId) → Future<List<OrderModel>>
  getOrdersBySeller(String sellerId) → Future<List<OrderModel>>
  updateOrderStatus(String orderId, String status) → Future<void>
  watchOrder(String orderId) → Stream<OrderModel>
  watchOrdersByUser(String userId) → Stream<List<OrderModel>>

cart_repository.dart
  saveCart(String userId, List<CartItemModel> items) → Future<void>
  loadCart(String userId) → Future<List<CartItemModel>>
  clearCart(String userId) → Future<void>

seller_repository.dart
  getSeller(String sellerId) → Future<SellerModel>
  updateSeller(SellerModel s) → Future<void>
  getSellerProducts(String sellerId) → Future<List<ProductModel>>
  getSellerOrders(String sellerId) → Future<List<OrderModel>>
  watchSellerOrders(String sellerId) → Stream<List<OrderModel>>

Repository rules:
  - Constructor injection for FirebaseFirestore + Database
  - All Firestore calls wrapped in try/catch
  - Rethrow as RepositoryException (create in utils/exceptions.dart)
  - No Flutter UI imports

